target: visitors
validations:
  - name: visitors_spawn_and_move
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that visitors spawn at the entrance and walk along paths.
        After building enclosures and laying paths from the entrance, small
        colored dots (visitors) should appear at the bottom-center entrance
        tile and move along the path tiles toward enclosures. They should
        follow the path rather than cutting through walls or enclosures.
  - name: visitors_view_enclosures
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that visitors stop at enclosures to view them. When a visitor
        reaches an enclosure's frontage, it should pause for a noticeable
        duration before moving on. After viewing, it should move to another
        enclosure or head back to the entrance. Visitors should not get
        stuck permanently at any location.
  - name: visitor_count_reflects_appeal
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that visitor volume correlates with zoo quality. A zoo with
        more animals and reasonable admission prices should show more
        visitors on screen than an empty or very expensive zoo. Adding
        animals and lowering prices should result in visibly more visitor
        dots moving through the zoo over time.
